meanings: COMB in N-COUNT -taker combines with nouns to form other nouns which refer to people who take things, for example decisions or notes.

A taker is any individual that is part of the 47% of Americans who pay zero federal income taxes...and then votes over and over for the party that is most likely to increase taxes (ie. take even more earned property) on the 53% who DO pay federal income taxes. These folks also do not have a hint ...
